{
  "stem": "268.9",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "Her name was Andre Bulova, which meant nothing to me until I came to the United States.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "We landed in Boston the 19th of November 1948.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "It was 50 years just recently.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I remembered for the first time in my life seeing lit up billboards.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we got on this train.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We passed the different stations.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I see billboards.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then we came to Times Square of New York.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We had to change trains.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I went to Indianapolis, Indiana.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We tried change trains in New York.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I kept looking at this big billboard in Times Square.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And it said, Bulova Watches.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And it turned out to be my sponsor was the president of, Andre Bulova of Bulova Watches.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "That's who signed my papers.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So I said to myself, gee, I must have a famous sponsor here.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I could have gone for a job.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I didn't, of course.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "But I did write him a letter later, in my broken English, thanking him for-- for-- for what he did.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "So that was my trip to the United States.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In boats, what we called troop carriers, which was a wonderful voyage.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "For one thing, the only downside of it was sea sickness, because this was November, and seas were kind of choppy.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But the beautiful part about it that food was-- this was a post-war year, but we never had enough of it.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Even in Austria, food was rationed.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And here, all of a sudden, I came on an American boat.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It was a troop carrier.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "You would line up in the cafeteria, and it was a tray three times a day.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And they give you-- I remember, for breakfast, I didn't know what it was.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But it had pieces of meat in it on toast.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
